But this only works inside Docker.

Stage 5 — Reverse Proxy (Nginx)

This is a real DevOps concept.

You added:

nginx container

Purpose:

Route requests.

Without nginx:

localhost:3000 → frontend
localhost:5000 → backend

With nginx:

localhost → frontend
localhost/api → backend

So users only see one entry point.

Example routing:

location /
→ frontend

location /api
→ backend
Stage 6 — API Gateway Style Routing

You implemented this:

Frontend request:

/api/health

Nginx rewrite:

/health

Forwarded to:

backend:5000

This is exactly how production systems work.

